    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1980-01-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1980-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <head>329. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>) to Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> and Secretary of Defense
                        <persName corresp="#p_BH_2">Brown</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d329fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 12, Egypt:
                        1–4/80. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1980-01-12">January 12, 1980</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Longer-Term Security Assistance to Egypt (C)</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has approved in principle the sale to Egypt of F–16 aircraft and
                    M–60 tanks, and this decision should be communicated to Vice President <persName
                        corresp="#p_MH_1">Mubarak</persName> during his upcoming visit. In addition,
                    the Egyptians should be informed that we would also authorize sale of the
                    intermediate export fighter (F–X), if developed. (S)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
